---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Tunisia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/tunisia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Morocco for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/morocco' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
  { title: 'Italy for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/italy' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'tunisiaFit', header: 'Tunisia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TND$1,500-2,140/mo', tunisiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TND$1,755-2,510/mo', tunisiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TND$1,350-1,930/mo', tunisiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TND$1,255-1,790/mo', tunisiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (STAR, Comar)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'TND$200-500/mo', tunisiaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'TND$1,350-2,140', annual: 'TND$16.2K-25.7K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'TND$1,850-2,855', annual: 'TND$22.2K-34.3K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'TND$2,490-3,835', annual: 'TND$29.9K-46K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'TND$50-150/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'TND$300-800/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Tunisia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Tunisia. Mediterranean beaches, Carthage ruins, French accessibility, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Tunisia"
  subheadline="Tunisia offers Mediterranean beaches, Carthage ruins, French language accessibility, and affordable living—North Africa's most liberal society with democratic aspirations."
  heroImage="/images/countries/tunisia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Tunisia</h2>
  <p>
    Tunisia offers Mediterranean beaches, Carthage and Roman ruins, French language accessibility, affordable living, and Arab world's most progressive society. For French-speaking retirees seeking Mediterranean lifestyle at modest cost, Tunisia provides excellent value with cultural richness.
  </p>

  <p>
    Tunis is the capital with best healthcare. Hammamet and Sousse offer resort lifestyles. Sidi Bou Said has picturesque charm. Djerba provides island living. Most expats choose coastal areas for lifestyle with Tunis healthcare accessible.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good medical tourism hub; affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; French widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> TND$2,000-4,000/month (~$650-1,300 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean; pleasant year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Progressive; cultured; Mediterranean</li>
      <li><strong>France proximity:</strong> 2-hour flight to Paris</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Tunisia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Tunisia is a medical tourism hub—Clinique Les Oliviers and private hospitals provide good care at low cost. Many doctors trained in France. Tunisia attracts medical tourists from Europe and Africa. Most conditions treatable locally; France provides backup for complex cases.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare very affordable. Medical tourism specialty. French-speaking healthcare. International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage and France access if needed.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Medical Tourism Hub</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Tunisia is established medical tourism destination. Good private hospitals at affordable prices. Many procedures attract European patients. French-speaking doctors. France provides backup for complex cases (2-hour flight to Paris).
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Tunisia has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Entry</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free for many Western nationalities. Good for exploration.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Extensions possible. Some use border runs for extended stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit (Carte de Séjour)</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories including retirement.
  </p>

  <h3>Property Ownership</h3>
  <p>
    Foreigners can buy property. Helps with residence applications.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Tunisia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> France/Europe coverage helpful</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Tunisia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with France/Europe coverage recommended. Local private care is good and very affordable. France provides backup for complex cases. Good value proposition for Mediterranean retirement.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Tunisia, Europe coverage beneficial:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Tunisia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Europe/MENA network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>France access:</strong> 2-hour flight to Paris</li>
    <li><strong>Local value:</strong> Affordable quality care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Tunisia retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Tunisia (TND ~3.1 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Local private:</strong> Medical tourism quality at low cost</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Very affordable local care</li>
    <li><strong>France network:</strong> Use for complex cases</li>
    <li><strong>Preventive care:</strong> Excellent local options</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: French Mediterranean Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,800/month pension. Residence card. Hammamet.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with France coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TND$1,600/month (~$515). Beach lifestyle; Paris backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Budget Maximizer, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,200/month pension. Residence card. Djerba.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with essential coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TND$1,400/month (~$450). Island living; value coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Culture Enthusiast, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,000/month income. Tourist rotation. Sidi Bou Said.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TND$1,800/month (~$580). Cultural immersion; global backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Tunisia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—tourist areas well-managed. Avoid Tunisia-Libya border region. Some security incidents in past but situation stable. Democratic transition ongoing. Normal precautions apply. Most expats feel secure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need French?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very helpful—French widely spoken in business, healthcare, tourism. Arabic is official but French is strong second language. Better French than Morocco in some ways. Healthcare fully accessible in French.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How progressive is Tunisia?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Most progressive in Arab world—women's rights advanced since 1956. Secular constitution. Alcohol available. Bikinis on beaches. Democratic transition since 2011 (Arab Spring origin). More liberal than neighbors.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Tunisia vs Morocco?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Tunisia more progressive, cheaper, less touristy. Morocco more exotic, better infrastructure, larger expat community. Tunisia better French accessibility. Morocco closer to Spain. Both excellent for French speakers seeking Mediterranean at low cost.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Tunisia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Tunisia authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
